    "what_description": "Micrechites minutiflorus is an evergreen climber in the family Apocynaceae, native to the tropical regions of Asia. The plant has a woody stem with a diameter of up to 1.5 mm and a length of up to 30 cm, with a simple, elliptical leaf with a length of 3-7 cm and a width of 1-3 cm. The leaves are glabrous, with a coriaceous texture, an acute apex and a cuneate base. The flowers are small, white, and unisexual, arranged in axillary clusters, with a calyx of 2 mm in length and a corolla of 2-3 mm. The inflorescence is a cymose raceme, with 2-4 flowers in each cyme.",
