    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Micrechites minutiflorus are its anti-inflammatory effects, which are attributed to the presence of flavonoids and saponins in the plant. This plant has been traditionally used to treat various health conditions, including fever and respiratory issues, such as bronchitis, due to the volatile oils present in its leaves. The bioactive compounds in Micrechites minutiflorus have also been found to possess antimicrobial properties, which are useful in preventing the growth of certain bacteria and fungi that cause infections. Furthermore, the plant's leaves have been used to treat gastrointestinal disorders, such as diarrhea, due to the presence of flavonoids that help in reducing inflammation in the digestive tract. Additionally, the plant's roots have been found to exhibit antioxidant properties, which help in protecting the body from oxidative stress and cell damage caused by free radicals.",
